	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What I'm wondering is how the 2nd company managed to change their name to Arduino and get away with it; that's trademark dilution if they're in the same line of business.<br /><br />Or, if the manufacturer changed their name first, imagine the situation where a sparkplug maker named &quot;A-1 Sparkplugs&quot; suddenly changed their name to &quot;Testarossa&quot; and then tried to sue Ferrari.<br /><br />Interesting to see what will happen.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
